body:
### Problem

As in the title, after 7342e6b00d - sounds like infinite loop somewhere. In such case I can stop nvim only by SIGKILL. @lewis6991 

### Steps to reproduce

`sem-tok.lua`:
```lua
local api = vim.api

vim.o.swapfile = false -- convenient after crash here

api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', {
  pattern = {'lua'},
  group = api.nvim_create_augroup('luals', {}),
  callback = function ()
    vim.lsp.start({
      name = 'luals',
      filetype = 'lua',
      cmd = {'lua-language-server'},
      root_dir = vim.uv.cwd(),
      settings = {
        Lua = {
          runtime = {
            path = {
              '?.lua',
              '?/init.lua',
            },
            version = 'LuaJIT',
            pathStrict = true,
          },
          workspace = {
            ignoreDir = {'lua'},
            checkThirdParty = false,
            library = {
              vim.fs.joinpath(vim.env.VIMRUNTIME, 'lua'),
              vim.fs.joinpath('${3rd}/luv/library', 'lua'),
            },
          },
          diagnostics = {
            globals = {'vim'},
          },
        },
      },
    })
  end,
})

vim.wo.foldmethod = 'expr'
vim.wo.foldexpr = 'v:lua.vim.treesitter.foldexpr()'
```
- `nvim  -u sem-tok.lua sem-tok.lua`
- wait for lua-ls

Alternatively, you can set `vim.go.foldlevelstart = 99 ` in init and observe hanging after typing `za` on a fold.

### Expected behavior

No regression

### Nvim version (nvim -v)

v0.11.0-dev-1114+gad3472e291

### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?

no

### Operating system/version

Debian Sid

### Terminal name/version

alacritty

### $TERM environment variable

alacritty

### Installation

from repo
